                            <comment id="12977853" author="stack" created="Wed, 5 Jan 2011 17:08:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Moving to 0.90.1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I cannot explain how in-memory state has OPENING for the node but the znode content is M_ZK_REGION_OFFLINE without more context.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12985543" author="billgraham" created="Mon, 24 Jan 2011 07:23:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I got myself into the same state. I was able to do this using 0.90.0-rc1 and CDH3b2 by either:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Changing COMPRESSION =&amp;gt; &apos;lzo&apos; on an existing table where lzo is not set up on HBase.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Creating a new table with COMPRESSION =&amp;gt; &apos;lzo&apos; where lzo is not set up on HBase.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;In my case though hbck -fix wouldn&apos;t work. I had to restart the cluster and then run hbck -fix. See this thread for more info:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://mail-archives.apache.org/mod_mbox/hbase-user/201101.mbox/%3CAANLkTi=GRWBhOVM=YjKMODfm8XyVN5T0XEkdb4FF2CrP@mail.gmail.com%3E&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://mail-archives.apache.org/mod_mbox/hbase-user/201101.mbox/%3CAANLkTi=GRWBhOVM=YjKMODfm8XyVN5T0XEkdb4FF2CrP@mail.gmail.com%3E&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12991697" author="tlipcon" created="Mon, 7 Feb 2011 23:17:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bumping to 0.90.2 since we haven&apos;t investigated enough&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13007890" author="clehene" created="Thu, 17 Mar 2011 11:03:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve seen this as well. At the same time the HRegionServer was getting a message to close the region, but since it wasn&apos;t actually serving it it was reporting an error as well creating this infinite loop.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13008308" author="stack" created="Fri, 18 Mar 2011 03:27:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I agree this is critical issue for 0.90.2.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13010560" author="stack" created="Thu, 24 Mar 2011 05:11:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t have enough info to figure whats going on here.  I want to punt to 0.90.3 until we have logs from actual fail.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13010563" author="stack" created="Thu, 24 Mar 2011 05:23:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I want to close this as dup of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3669&quot; title=&quot;Region in PENDING_OPEN keeps being bounced between RS and master&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-3669&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-3669&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; if thats ok.  &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3669&quot; title=&quot;Region in PENDING_OPEN keeps being bounced between RS and master&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-3669&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-3669&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; has more helpful log.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13010755" author="jdcryans" created="Thu, 24 Mar 2011 16:38:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah, they seem to be different instances of the same issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13010829" author="stack" created="Thu, 24 Mar 2011 18:38:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Marking as duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3669&quot; title=&quot;Region in PENDING_OPEN keeps being bounced between RS and master&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-3669&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-3669&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (Please reopen if anyone disagrees)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15016911" author="lars_francke" created="Fri, 20 Nov 2015 12:41:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue was closed as part of a bulk closing operation on 2015-11-20. All issues that have been resolved and where all fixVersions have been released have been closed (following discussions on the mailing list).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
